"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(*)\nFROM client\nJOIN district ON client.district_id = district.district_id\nWHERE client.birth_date LIKE '1920%' AND district.A3 = 'east Bohemia';\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of clients who were born in 1920 and are located in the region of east Bohemia. It joins the `client` table with the `district` table using the `district_id` foreign key relationship and filters the results based on the birth year and region."